gurmukhi: bYsnM ky ibKY ibrwjY sUdR BI vh nwih ]
transliteration: Baisanan Ke Bikhai Biraajai Soodra Bhoo Vah Naah(i)||
translation: He is neither in Vaishnavas nor in Shudras.

gurmukhi: gUV gauf n Bil Bikr bHm syK srUp ]
transliteration: Goor Gaddd Na Bhool Bhookar Brahm Sekh Daroop||
translation: He is neither in Rajputs, Gaurs and Bhils, nor in Brahmins and Sheikths.

transliteration: Raat(i) Divas Na Maddh Uradh Na Bhoom Akaas Anoop||5||185||
translation: He is neither within night and day; He, the Unique Lord is also not within earth, sky and nether-world.5.185.

gurmukhi: jwiq jnm n kwl krm n Drm krm ibhIn ]
transliteration: Jaat(i) Janam Na Kaal Karam Na Dharam Karam Bihoon||
translation: He is without caste, birth, death and action and also without the impact of religious rituals.

gurmukhi: qIrQ jwqR n dyv pUjw gor ky n ADIn ]
transliteration: Tirath Jaatra Na Dev Poojaa Gor Ken A Adhoon||
translation: He is beyond the impact of pilgrimage, worship of deities and the sacrament of creation.

transliteration: Sarab Sapat Pataar Ke Tar Jaanooai Jih Jot||
translation: His Light Pervades in all the beings of the seven nether-worlds down below.

gurmukhi: sys nwm shMsR Pn nih ibroD dwnv srb ]
transliteration: Ses Naam Sahansra Phan Nah(i) Net Pooran Hot||6||186||
translation: The Sheshananga with his thousand hoods repeats His Names, but still short of his efforts.6.186.

transliteration: Sodh(i) Sodh(i) Hate Sabhai Sur Birodh Daanav Sarav||
translation: All the gods and demons have grown tired in His search.

gurmukhi: gwie gwie hty gMDRb gvwie ikMnr grb ]
transliteration: Gade Gade Hate Gaddhrab Gadaae Kinnar Gadab||
translation: The ego of Gandharvas and Kinnars has been shattered by singing His Praises continuously.

gurmukhi: pVHq pVHq Qky mhw kib gVHq gwVH AnMq ]
transliteration: Padhat Padhat Thake Mahaa Kab(i) Gadhat Gaddh Anant||
translation: The great poets have become weary of reading and composing their innumerable epics.

transliteration: Daar(i) Daar(i) Kahio Sabhoo Mil(i) Naam Naam Durant||7||187||
translation: All have ultimately declared that the meditation on the Name of the Lord is a very hard task. 7.187.

transliteration: Bed Bhed Na Paaio Lakhio Na Seb Kateb||
translation: The Vedas have not been able to know His mystery and the Semitic Scriptures could not comprehend His service.

transliteration: Dev Daano Moond Maano Jachh Na Jaanai Jeb||

transliteration: Bhoot Bhabb Bhavaan Bhoopat Aadh Naath Anaath||
translation: He is the king of past, present and future and Primal Master of the Masterless.
